<div id="intro">
  IMDbPY is a Python package for retrieving and managing the data of the IMDb movie database about movies, people, and companies.
</div>

<p>
  <a href="/downloads" class="button primary-button">Downloads</a>
  <a href="https://imdbpy.readthedocs.io/" class="button secondary-button">Read the Docs</a>
</p>

<div>
  <ul>
    <li>Written in pure Python 3.</li>
    <li>Platform-independent.</li>
    <li>Can retrieve data from both the IMDb's web server and a local copy of the whole database.</li>
    <li>Released under the terms of the <a href="https://github.com/alberanid/imdbpy/blob/master/docs/LICENSE.txt">GPL 2 license.</a></li>
    <li>A simple API.</li>
    <li>IMDbPY is used by many other projects. <a href="#">Curious about that?</a></li>
  </ul>
</div>

<section>
  <h2>Code example</h2>
<pre>
<code class="microlight">
from imdb import IMDb

# create an instance of the IMDb class
ia = IMDb()

# get a movie and print its director(s)
the_matrix = ia.get_movie('0133093')
print(the_matrix['director'])

# show all information sets avaiable for movies
print(ia.get_movie_infoset())
</code>
</pre>
</section>

